expected_issues.suggested_fix:
Wrap email sending in try/catch block, log error with context, and return success/failure status. Example:

try {
  await emailClient.send({ ... });
  return { success: true };
} catch (error) {
  logger.error('Failed to send welcome email', { userId, error });
  return { success: false, error: error.message };
}

Either await the call with error handling, or add .catch() to handle errors:

sendNotification(userId, message).catch(error => {
  logger.error('Failed to send notification', { userId, error });
});

expected_tests.test_code:
it('handles email service failure', async () => {
  jest.spyOn(emailClient, 'send').mockRejectedValue(new Error('Service down'));
  const result = await sendWelcomeEmail(1);
  expect(result.success).toBe(false);
  expect(result.error).toContain('Service down');
});

it('returns success when email sends', async () => {
  jest.spyOn(emailClient, 'send').mockResolvedValue(undefined);
  const result = await sendWelcomeEmail(1);
  expect(result.success).toBe(true);
});

